olved, but meaningful native-image coverage of mocking needs Mockito's proxy mock maker test resource rather than the default inline mock maker.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Add a test resource at src/test/resources/mockito-extensions/org.mockito.plugins.MockMaker containing exactly org.mockito.internal.creation.proxy.ProxyMockMaker. Keep coverage interface-based, because ProxyMockMaker uses JDK proxies and supports interfaces only; avoid class/final-class mocking and inline mock-maker assumptions in native-image tests.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The core artifact is Scala-first; Java tests can exercise parts of the API but Scala macro/TypeTag-heavy APIs may be awkward without Scala test source support.\",\n    \"Using Mockito's default inline mock maker or mocking concrete classes is likely to fail or be unsupported under Native Image.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_00482493145a2d59016a28d2becbd88190ba3413c8d852b18e\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 427, "output": 627, "cacheRead": 29696, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30750, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1781060277651, "responseId": "resp_00482493145a2d59016a28d2b677d48190a8caa61ce1658ac7"}}
